**Code Explanation:**

The following script performs a full trajectory rollout from t=0 to t=5.0 (500 steps) for the 20 held-out validation simulations. It integrates the initial conditions using the standard leapfrog scheme, first with the ground-truth analytical Newtonian gravity (with softening epsilon=0.01) and then using the trained Graph Neural Network (GNN) as the learned force field. At each step, the total energy (Kinetic + Potential, in normalized units M L^2 / T^2) is computed to monitor the Hamiltonian conservation. The script calculates the relative energy error |E_final - E_initial| / |E_initial| for both the ground truth and the GNN, as well as the Mean Squared Error (MSE) of the final positions and velocities to quantify the trajectory drift. Finally, it generates a 4x5 multi-panel plot comparing the time evolution of the total energy for the GNN versus the ground truth across all 20 validation simulations. If the GNN energy diverges significantly, the y-axis is clipped to maintain visibility of the ground-truth baseline.

